Changes in Chordii 4.6.0

Coloured chords!

Command line option --chord-colour can be used to select one of the
values 'black', 'white', 'red', 'green', 'blue', 'yellow', 'magenta'
and 'cyan'. For example

  --chord-colour=blue

In ChordPro and .chordrc files, the directive 'chordcolour' can be
used, e.g.

  {chordcolour: blue}

Arbitrary colours can be specified using the conventional hexadecimal
notation '#RRGGBB', e.g., '#87CEEB' would be sky blue.

See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Html_color

Other changes:

* Allow zero value for -x (transpose). Warn on illegal or insane
  values.
